### isKnownNonConstant() {#ad922c9d738ce5ff795e0b876b4ee30b0}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>static bool isKnownNonConstant (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/value">Value</a> &#42; V)</>}
  labels = {["static"]}>
Returns true if we can statically tell that this value will never be a &quot;useful&quot; constant.

In practice, this means we&#39;ve got something like an alloca or a malloc call for which a comparison against a constant can only be guarding dead code. Note that we are potentially giving up some precision in dead code (a constant result) in favour of avoiding a expensive search for a easily answered common query.

Definition at line <a href="#l01756">1756</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/analysis/lazyvalueinfo-cpp">LazyValueInfo.cpp</a>.
</MemberDefinition>

<Link id="l00240" /><CodeLine lineNumber="240"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// When an edge in the graph has been threaded, values that we could not</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00241" /><CodeLine lineNumber="241"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// determine a value for before (i.e. were marked overdefined) may be</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00242" /><CodeLine lineNumber="242"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// possible to solve now. We do NOT try to proactively update these values.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00243" /><CodeLine lineNumber="243"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Instead, we clear their entries from the cache, and allow lazy updating to</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00244" /><CodeLine lineNumber="244"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// recompute them when needed.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00245" /><CodeLine lineNumber="245"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00246" /><CodeLine lineNumber="246"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// The updating process is fairly simple: we need to drop cached info</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00247" /><CodeLine lineNumber="247"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// for all values that were marked overdefined in OldSucc, and for those same</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00248" /><CodeLine lineNumber="248"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// values in any successor of OldSucc (except NewSucc) in which they were</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00249" /><CodeLine lineNumber="249"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// also marked overdefined.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00250" /><CodeLine lineNumber="250"><span class="doxyHighlight">  std::vector&lt;BasicBlock&#42;&gt; worklist;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00251" /><CodeLine lineNumber="251"><span class="doxyHighlight">  worklist.push&#95;back(OldSucc);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00252" /><CodeLine lineNumber="252"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00253" /><CodeLine lineNumber="253"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">const</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> BlockCacheEntry &#42;Entry = getBlockEntry(OldSucc);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00254" /><CodeLine lineNumber="254"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (!Entry || Entry-&gt;OverDefined.empty())</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00255" /><CodeLine lineNumber="255"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">return</span><span class="doxyHighlight">; </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Nothing to process here.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00256" /><CodeLine lineNumber="256"><span class="doxyHighlight">  <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/smallvector">SmallVector&lt;Value &#42;, 4&gt;</a> ValsToClear(Entry-&gt;OverDefined.begin(),</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00257" /><CodeLine lineNumber="257"><span class="doxyHighlight">                                      Entry-&gt;OverDefined.end());</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00258" /><CodeLine lineNumber="258"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00259" /><CodeLine lineNumber="259"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Use a worklist to perform a depth-first search of OldSucc&#39;s successors.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00260" /><CodeLine lineNumber="260"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// NOTE: We do not need a visited list since any blocks we have already</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00261" /><CodeLine lineNumber="261"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// visited will have had their overdefined markers cleared already, and we</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00262" /><CodeLine lineNumber="262"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// thus won&#39;t loop to their successors.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00263" /><CodeLine lineNumber="263"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">while</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (!worklist.empty()) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00264" /><CodeLine lineNumber="264"><span class="doxyHighlight">    <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/basicblock">BasicBlock</a> &#42;ToUpdate = worklist.back();</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00265" /><CodeLine lineNumber="265"><span class="doxyHighlight">    worklist.pop&#95;back();</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00266" /><CodeLine lineNumber="266"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00267" /><CodeLine lineNumber="267"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Skip blocks only accessible through NewSucc.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00268" /><CodeLine lineNumber="268"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (ToUpdate == NewSucc) </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">continue</span><span class="doxyHighlight">;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00269" /><CodeLine lineNumber="269"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00270" /><CodeLine lineNumber="270"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// If a value was marked overdefined in OldSucc, and is here too...</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00271" /><CodeLine lineNumber="271"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">auto</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> OI = BlockCache.find&#95;as(ToUpdate);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00272" /><CodeLine lineNumber="272"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (OI == BlockCache.end() || OI-&gt;second-&gt;OverDefined.empty())</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00273" /><CodeLine lineNumber="273"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">continue</span><span class="doxyHighlight">;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00274" /><CodeLine lineNumber="274"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">auto</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> &amp;ValueSet = OI-&gt;second-&gt;OverDefined;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00275" /><CodeLine lineNumber="275"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00276" /><CodeLine lineNumber="276"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">bool</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> changed = </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">false</span><span class="doxyHighlight">;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00277" /><CodeLine lineNumber="277"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">for</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/value">Value</a> &#42;V : ValsToClear) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00278" /><CodeLine lineNumber="278"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (!ValueSet.erase(V))</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00280" /><CodeLine lineNumber="280"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00281" /><CodeLine lineNumber="281"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// If we removed anything, then we potentially need to update</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00282" /><CodeLine lineNumber="282"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// blocks successors too.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00283" /><CodeLine lineNumber="283"><span class="doxyHighlight">      changed = </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">true</span><span class="doxyHighlight">;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00284" /><CodeLine lineNumber="284"><span class="doxyHighlight">    &#125;</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00286" /><CodeLine lineNumber="286"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (!changed) </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">continue</span><span class="doxyHighlight">;</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00462" /><CodeLine lineNumber="462"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00463" /><CodeLine lineNumber="463"><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">void</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> LazyValueInfoImpl::solve() &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00464" /><CodeLine lineNumber="464"><span class="doxyHighlight">  <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#a8fc529c79977cdd01e187986f960a07f">SmallVector&lt;std::pair&lt;BasicBlock &#42;, Value &#42;&gt;</a>, 8&gt; StartingStack =</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00465" /><CodeLine lineNumber="465"><span class="doxyHighlight">      BlockValueStack;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00466" /><CodeLine lineNumber="466"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00467" /><CodeLine lineNumber="467"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">unsigned</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> processedCount = 0;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00468" /><CodeLine lineNumber="468"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">while</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (!BlockValueStack.empty()) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00469" /><CodeLine lineNumber="469"><span class="doxyHighlight">    processedCount++;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00470" /><CodeLine lineNumber="470"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Abort if we have to process too many values to get a result for this one.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00471" /><CodeLine lineNumber="471"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Because of the design of the overdefined cache currently being per-block</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00472" /><CodeLine lineNumber="472"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// to avoid naming-related issues (IE it wants to try to give different</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00473" /><CodeLine lineNumber="473"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// results for the same name in different blocks), overdefined results don&#39;t</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00474" /><CodeLine lineNumber="474"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// get cached globally, which in turn means we will often try to rediscover</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00475" /><CodeLine lineNumber="475"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// the same overdefined result again and again.  Once something like</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00476" /><CodeLine lineNumber="476"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// PredicateInfo is used in LVI or CVP, we should be able to make the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00477" /><CodeLine lineNumber="477"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// overdefined cache global, and remove this throttle.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00478" /><CodeLine lineNumber="478"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (processedCount &gt; <a href="#a606f0f9e7e2731b55f11e30247033341">MaxProcessedPerValue</a>) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00479" /><CodeLine lineNumber="479"><span class="doxyHighlight">      <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/support/debug-h/#a196897517069dda1bdb549e24468f7d7">LLVM&#95;DEBUG</a>(</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00480" /><CodeLine lineNumber="480"><span class="doxyHighlight">          <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#a7c46c742c31be54870e2038048e6b391">dbgs</a>() &lt;&lt; </span><span class="doxyHighlightStringLiteral">&quot;Giving up on stack because we are getting too deep\\n&quot;</span><span class="doxyHighlight">);</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00676" /><CodeLine lineNumber="676"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Loop over all of our predecessors, merging what we know from them into</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00677" /><CodeLine lineNumber="677"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// result.  If we encounter an unexplored predecessor, we eagerly explore it</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00678" /><CodeLine lineNumber="678"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// in a depth first manner.  In practice, this has the effect of discovering</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00679" /><CodeLine lineNumber="679"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// paths we can&#39;t analyze eagerly without spending compile times analyzing</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00680" /><CodeLine lineNumber="680"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// other paths.  This heuristic benefits from the fact that predecessors are</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00681" /><CodeLine lineNumber="681"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// frequently arranged such that dominating ones come first and we quickly</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00682" /><CodeLine lineNumber="682"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// find a path to function entry.  TODO: We should consider explicitly</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00683" /><CodeLine lineNumber="683"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// canonicalizing to make this true rather than relying on this happy</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00684" /><CodeLine lineNumber="684"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// accident.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00685" /><CodeLine lineNumber="685"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">for</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (BasicBlock &#42;Pred : <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#acb22fb04083152eee862457e42e8dc31">predecessors</a>(BB)) &#123;</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l01907" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1907"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01908" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1908"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Note: The following bit of code is somewhat distinct from the rest of LVI;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01909" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1909"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// LVI as a whole tries to compute a lattice value which is conservatively</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01910" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1910"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// correct at a given location.  In this case, we have a predicate which we</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01911" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1911"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// weren&#39;t able to prove about the merged result, and we&#39;re pushing that</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01912" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1912"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// predicate back along each incoming edge to see if we can prove it</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01913" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1913"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// separately for each input.  As a motivating example, consider:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01914" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1914"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// bb1:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01915" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1915"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   %v1 = ... ; constantrange&lt;1, 5&gt;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01916" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1916"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   br label %merge</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01917" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1917"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// bb2:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01918" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1918"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   %v2 = ... ; constantrange&lt;10, 20&gt;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01919" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1919"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   br label %merge</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01920" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1920"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// merge:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01921" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1921"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   %phi = phi &#91;%v1, %v2&#93; ; constantrange&lt;1,20&gt;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01922" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1922"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   %pred = icmp eq i32 %phi, 8</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01923" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1923"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// We can&#39;t tell from the lattice value for &#39;%phi&#39; that &#39;%pred&#39; is false</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01924" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1924"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// along each path, but by checking the predicate over each input separately,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01925" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1925"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// we can.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01926" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1926"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// We limit the search to one step backwards from the current BB and value.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01927" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1927"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// We could consider extending this to search further backwards through the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01928" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1928"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// CFG and/or value graph, but there are non-obvious compile time vs quality</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01929" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1929"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// tradeoffs.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01930" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1930"><span class="doxyHighlight">  <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/basicblock">BasicBlock</a> &#42;BB = CxtI-&gt;<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/ilist-detail/node-parent-access/#a7e19e7508415378ad9523e0339b23e22">getParent</a>();</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01931" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1931"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01932" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1932"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Function entry or an unreachable block.  Bail to avoid confusing</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01933" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1933"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// analysis below.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01934" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1934"><span class="doxyHighlight">  <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#ab5b46bfb4c91a29504b08dacfeb04a6c">pred&#95;iterator</a> PI = <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#ac3e549d97549636a7f08779d5cd98540">pred&#95;begin</a>(BB), PE = <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#a2103c335fa6ab933312c3871c82b0106">pred&#95;end</a>(BB);</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l01937" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1937"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01938" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1938"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// If V is a PHI node in the same block as the context, we need to ask</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01939" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1939"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// questions about the predicate as applied to the incoming value along</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01940" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1940"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// each edge. This is useful for eliminating cases where the predicate is</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l01942" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1942"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (</span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">auto</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> &#42;<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/amdgpu/amdgpurewriteundefforphi-cpp/#a2e83cb1bc3f5e8986cbd14575755a134">PHI</a> = <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#a22eeee01734061ac1b31ccd994c49eef">dyn&#95;cast&lt;PHINode&gt;</a>(V))</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01943" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1943"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/amdgpu/amdgpurewriteundefforphi-cpp/#a2e83cb1bc3f5e8986cbd14575755a134">PHI</a>-&gt;getParent() == BB) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01944" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1944"><span class="doxyHighlight">      <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/constant">Constant</a> &#42;Baseline = </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">nullptr</span><span class="doxyHighlight">;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01945" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1945"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">for</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (</span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">unsigned</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> i = 0, e = <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/amdgpu/amdgpurewriteundefforphi-cpp/#a2e83cb1bc3f5e8986cbd14575755a134">PHI</a>-&gt;getNumIncomingValues(); i &lt; e; i++) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01946" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1946"><span class="doxyHighlight">        <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/value">Value</a> &#42;<a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/incoming">Incoming</a> = <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/amdgpu/amdgpurewriteundefforphi-cpp/#a2e83cb1bc3f5e8986cbd14575755a134">PHI</a>-&gt;getIncomingValue(i);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01947" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1947"><span class="doxyHighlight">        <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/basicblock">BasicBlock</a> &#42;PredBB = <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/amdgpu/amdgpurewriteundefforphi-cpp/#a2e83cb1bc3f5e8986cbd14575755a134">PHI</a>-&gt;getIncomingBlock(i);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01948" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1948"><span class="doxyHighlight">        </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Note that PredBB may be BB itself.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01949" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1949"><span class="doxyHighlight">        <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/constant">Constant</a> &#42;Result =</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01950" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1950"><span class="doxyHighlight">            <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/lazyvalueinfo/#a30223a7e41ce3064f9d85b3fe3ee7005">getPredicateOnEdge</a>(Pred, <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/incoming">Incoming</a>, <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/callingconv/#ac6aa1387c4375260e2468eb5a77fdb4cafd841a49aec1539bc88abc8ff9e170fb">C</a>, PredBB, BB, CxtI);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01951" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1951"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01952" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1952"><span class="doxyHighlight">        </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Keep going as long as we&#39;ve seen a consistent known result for</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01953" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1953"><span class="doxyHighlight">        </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// all inputs.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01954" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1954"><span class="doxyHighlight">        Baseline = (i == 0) ? Result </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/&#42; First iteration &#42;/</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01955" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1955"><span class="doxyHighlight">                            : (Baseline == Result ? Baseline</span></CodeLine>
